d smaller wattles, and are less glossy overall. Like most starlings, the Sri Lanka myna is fairly omnivorous, eating fruit, nectar and insects. In culture In Sri Lanka, the Myna bird is known in many names including Sela lihiniya, Mal kawadiya, Kampatiya in the Sinhala language. The name Sela Lihiniya is often mentioned in poems and other similar literature and is quoted for its melodious calls. This bird appears in a 10 rupee Sri Lankan postal stamp. It is also the media icon of Sri Lanka Rupavahini Corporation. References Birds of India by Grimmett, Inskipp and Inskipp, ISBN 0-691-04910-6 External links Image at ADW", "shortSummary": "The Sri Lanka hill myna or Ceylon myna (Gracula ptilogenys) is a myna, a member of the starling family. This bird is endemic to Sri Lanka.", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7c/Flickr_-_Rainbirder_-_Ceylon_Myna_%28Gracula_ptilogenys%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-gracula", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-gracula-ptilogenys", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-gracula", "species": "taxonomy-species-gracula-ptilogenys"}, "expandable": true, "x": -93.16, "y": -768.02, "z": 535.44}], "links": [{"key": "bird-sri-lanka-hill-myna-c6a6baab__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-gracula-ptilogenys", "source": "bird-sri-lanka-hill-myna-c6a6baab", "target": "taxonomy-species-gracula-ptilogenys", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-gracula-ptilogenys__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-gracula", "source": "taxonomy-species-gracula-ptilogenys", "target": "taxonomy-genus-gracula", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Sri Lanka hill myna 属于属 Gracula。"}]}
